<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-689-152  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 689 152.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>ESD: The Electronic System Design Magazine  August 1989 v19 n8p24(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New PLD resources tighten design. (Advanced Micro Devices andSignetics introduce programmable logic devices) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Phillips, Barry.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Signetics Co introduces the PLC42VA12, a programmable logic device(PLD) that includes a pin that enables the handling ofcombinatorial I-O while treating a bypassed register function as aburied register.andP;  The buried register and the combinatorial I-Ooperate independently, with all ten output macrocells beingprogrammable in five configurations and 20 variations depending onselection of register functions, type of flipflop, and internal orexternal clock sources.andP;  The PLC42VA12 is functionally a supersetof Advanced Micro Devices's (AMD) popular 22V10 PLD, as theSignetics' device includes two fully programmable arrays, theflexible output macrocells, and ELSE logic.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Signetics Corp. (products).andO;Product:   Signetics PLC 42VA12 (Integrated circuit) (design andconstruction).andO;Topic:     SpecificationsGate Arrays.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Architecture of the Signetics PLC42VA12. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>